        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/rescuers-evacuate-wounded-person-russian-missile-strike-sumy-ukraine.png" alt="Rescuers and volunteers evacuate a wounded person from an apartment building damaged during a Russian missile strike amid Russia's attack on Ukraine in Sumy" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Rescuers and volunteers evacuate a wounded person from an apartment building damaged during a Russian missile strike amid Russia's attack on Ukraine in Sumy. Credits: REUTERS/Stringer Purchase Licensing Rights
          </i></p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">US and Russian representatives met in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-03-2025-h1-1-negotiate-a-potential-ceasefire" target="_blank">negotiate a potential ceasefire</a> in Ukraine behind closed doors. The White House says achieving security in the Black Sea to allow the free flow of shipping is a key purpose of the talks. The US delegation comprised Special Envoy for Ukraine Keith Kellogg and National Security Advisor Mike Waltz.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Ukrainian FM Andrii Sybiha criticized Russia. While the talks were taking place, another missile hit Sumy and damaged several buildings, including a school, and 74 people were wounded. Sybiha stated that diplomacy with Russia "must be backed by firepower, sanctions, and pressure" to be effective. A Russian source told Reuters that a draft joint statement had been sent to Moscow and Washington for approval.
       </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Ukrainian leadership met with US leadership before the talks on Sunday and held follow-up discussions after the US-Russia meeting. There are claims that a new Ukrainian mineral deal is in the works and will be signed soon. The talks ended late Monday evening with no immediate word on an agreement. 
</p>
