          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Second Lady to visit Greenland</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/usha-vance-visit-greenland-us-delegation-danish-territory.png" alt="Usha Vance will visit Greenland on Thursday as part of a U.S. delegation to the Danish territory" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Usha Vance will visit Greenland on Thursday as part of a U.S. delegation to the Danish territory. Credits: Allison Joyce / AP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Tensions between Greenland and the US continue to escalate after US officials, including Second Lady Usha Vance, announced an upcoming visit. Greenland‚Äôs Prime Minister Mute B. Egede denounced it as ‚Äúhighly aggressive.‚Äù The visit follows President Trump‚Äôs vow to annex Greenland, citing its rare earth minerals and Arctic strategic value. Trump has insisted the visit is about ‚Äú<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-03-2025-h2-2-friendliness-not-provocation" target="_blank">friendliness, not provocation</a>.‚Äù
</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Egede criticized US National Security Adviser Mike Waltz‚Äôs involvement. He is accusing the US of trying to assert power over Greenland. Egede‚Äôs left-wing party recently lost elections, but he remains in office during coalition talks. Jens-Frederik Nielsen, likely Greenland‚Äôs next leader, also condemned the timing as disrespectful. The White House frames the visit as cultural and focuses on attending Greenland‚Äôs national dogsled race.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Despite repeated rejections of annexation, Greenland remains open to economic cooperation. Denmark stresses respect for sovereignty. A recent poll showed 85% of Greenlanders oppose joining the US, with many viewing Trump‚Äôs interest as a threat.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
