          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá∞üá∑ South Korean court dismisses impeachment of PM Han Duck-soo</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          South Korea‚Äôs Constitutional Court has reinstated PM Han Duck-soo as acting president. His impeachment <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-03-2025-br1-4-case-was-dismissed" target="_blank">case was dismissed</a> in a 7-1 ruling. Han was suspended for refusing to appoint additional Constitutional Court justices. The court found insufficient grounds for his impeachment. Han pledges to focus on national unity and geopolitical challenges, urging an end to political division.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The court continues deliberating President Yoon Suk Yeol's fate. A ruling on Yoon is expected soon, requiring six of eight justices to uphold his impeachment for permanent removal. Yoon also faces criminal charges, which could result in life imprisonment or the death penalty if convicted. If Yoon is stripped of the presidency, an election must be held within 60 days.</p>
