            <strong>üá©üá™ Germany is unlocking billions to supercharge its military </strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Germany is significantly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-03-2025-br2-5-increasing-its-military-spending" target="_blank">increasing its military spending</a> in response to growing global threats and Russia‚Äôs war in Ukraine. Incoming Chancellor Friedrich Merz is leading efforts to strengthen Germany's underfunded military. He aims to spend 3.5% of GDP, around ‚Ç¨600 billion over the next decade. This marks Germany‚Äôs most extensive defense investment since the Cold War.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The German military faces challenges like outdated infrastructure, missed recruitment targets, and an aging force. A recent report warned the military ‚Äústill has too little of everything.‚Äù Merz is considering reintroducing mandatory service to boost numbers. Last year, Germany met NATO‚Äôs 2% defense spending target for the first time in 30 years. Public support is growing, with 66% backing increased military funding.</p>
        </mj-text>
